# Styling & Responsive Patterns

This file consolidates styling and responsive UI patterns (Tailwind + responsive rules).

## Tailwind & Styling

This project uses TailwindCSS 4 with JIT. Use Tailwind utility classes in components and prefer theme colors from `globals.css` / Tailwind config.

### Reusable Components & Utilities

Create styled component wrappers for consistency (buttons, cards, inputs). Use `className` templates or `classnames`.

### Accessibility & Focus

Always include visible focus states and ensure color contrast meets accessibility guidelines.

## Responsive UI Patterns

Follow mobile-first approach and Tailwind breakpoints. Prefer extending existing patterns and avoid ad-hoc breakpoints.

### Attendance Board & Layout

Use grid and responsive classes (`grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4`), and ensure no horizontal scroll at small widths.

### Modals & Tables

Use `BaseModal` for dialogs; body scrolls inside modal. For data tables, prefer stacked/card views on mobile and table on larger screens.

### Touch Targets

Ensure primary actions and icon buttons meet minimum touch target sizes (44x44px).

